 Phased reorganization of May-Must-Analysis

 Context

 Why this change. The codebase is ~25k LOC across files that mostly exceed 1000 lines (adapter.rs 3023, loops.rs 1527, backward.rs 1458,
 llvm_wrap.rs 1263, abstract_cfg.rs 1141, chc.rs 1002, rules.rs 981, driver.rs 976). To work on any one phase of the analyzer, an agent must
 read 5+ huge files, blowing the context budget before editing begins. The current top-level split (src/{common, may_must_analysis,
 absint_analysis}/) is by kind of code (shared vs. analysis-specific), not by pipeline phase, so a single phase concern (e.g. "loop invariant
 verifier") is scattered across loops.rs, backward.rs, chc.rs, and the LLM modules.

 Intended outcome. Reorganize into one top-level directory per pipeline phase, each with a short component.md describing purpose, public API,
 contract with neighbors, and what is not done there. An agent working on, e.g., DART can load forward_must/component.md + forward_must/dart.rs
  + the upstream cfg_prep/component.md and have everything needed without reading the rest of the tree. Also: delete unsound shortcuts (Phase 1
  + Phase 1b summary seeds) and clearly-orphaned modules (absint_analysis/, expressions/, most of assertions/, main.rs_bak, dead summaries
 helpers) that the user has flagged as not fitting paper-equivalence.

 Strategy. 8 phases. Each phase ends with a clean cargo build --release && cargo test -- --test-threads=1, then commit-and-push. Each phase is
 a self-contained checkpoint so a context reset between phases is safe. Cleanup precedes moves so we move less code.

