 Each component dir gets a short README (~150-300 lines) with this skeleton:

 # <component>

 ## Purpose
 <one paragraph: what pipeline phase this is, what it owns>

 ## Public API
 <table of types/functions exposed via `mod.rs`, one-line each>

 ## Inputs
 <what this component consumes from upstream — names + types + invariants assumed>

 ## Outputs
 <what this component produces — names + types + invariants guaranteed>

 ## Files
 <one-line per .rs file in this dir>

 ## Out of scope
 <things callers might expect here but live elsewhere — pointer to where>

 ## Contract with neighbors
 <who calls in, who this calls out to, what guarantees are exchanged>

 Plus one top-level docs/architecture.md (~400-600 lines) with the full pipeline diagram, the two-pillar invariant, the cross-component
 contracts, and a module quick-reference table.

